<p itemprop="description">Enterprise architecture involves designing and maintaining the overall structure of an organisation's business processes, information systems, and technology infrastructure to ensure alignment with strategic objectives and efficient operations.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand the role of enterprise architecture in organisational design and recognise how different architectural domains (business, data, application, technology) relate to each other.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can contribute to enterprise architecture activities, understand architectural principles and standards, and create basic architectural documentation under guidance.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can design enterprise architecture solutions, lead architectural assessments, establish architectural principles, and ensure alignment between business strategy and technology implementation.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can establish enterprise architecture strategy and governance, lead organisation-wide architectural transformation, and influence strategic decision-making through architectural insight.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

